reviewText: The movie is OK; it's not my favorite, but I didn't think it was awful. It's probably less entertaining to adults than to small fry, but it has its moments. The closed captions are EXCELLENT, but I couldn't find that any of the extra stuff was captioned, which is a shame because some of the ecology/endangered species material is pretty interesting.

reviewText: Did we leave the ranch, and then didn't get prepared to go to college? Or return to senior year of high school and not take a single college prep course? That part was thin. And it was nice to know that everyone knew she could talk to animals this time--rather than the HIDE THE ABILITY routine. Lucky rocks, he gets the best lines in all the moives.
Title: Dr. Dolittle: Tail To The Chief Repackaged

reviewText: Daughter of the famous 'Dr. Dolittle' is called to Washington D.C. to help the president's dog, Daisy, return to her former loveable self. Trouble aplenty with animals galore (of course she understands them but does she understand herself?). Add the daughter of the president, international intrigue and a rainforest to save . . . thin storyline but it isn't supposed to be serious. Lessons in life 101!
Title: Dr. Dolittle: Tail To The Chief Repackaged
